window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>She wasn’t looking for redemption. But in a charming Southern town full of heart, she just might find her purpose—and her match.</p> <p>Big-city marketing executive Norah Burke is used to fixing problems with polish and pitch. But when a project goes off the rails in ways she never expected, she heads south for a breather—landing in Wishful, Mississippi, the hometown of her best friend and the very definition of small-town charm.</p> <p>Cam Crawford has watched his beloved Wishful slowly crumble in the wake of economic hardship. He’s a man of the soil, rooted in community and responsibility, fighting to preserve what matters most. The last thing he needs is a savvy outsider stirring things up—even one with eyes that challenge his resolve and a plan that just might work.</p> <p>Thrown together by fate and fueled by a shared desire to save the town, Norah and Cam strike sparks and clash wills. But as business turns to something far more personal, they’ll have to decide whether they're willing to risk their hearts to build something lasting—together.</p> <p>Warm, witty, and deeply romantic, To Get Me To You is the unforgettable beginning to the Wishful series—a small-town love story about finding your place, healing old wounds, and choosing love when it matters most. Perfect for fans of Kristen Proby, Jill Shalvis, and small-town Southern swoon.</p>"; 
